    "Body": "Apply Now Financial Analyst II at Robinhood (View all jobs) Lake Mary, FL About the company Robinhood is democratizing our financial system. With customers at the heart of our decisions, Robinhood is lowering barriers, removing fees, and providing greater access to financial information. Together, we are building products and services that help create a financial system everyone can participate in.Â  Robinhood is a fast-growing company and was recognized as a CNBC Disruptor 50 and a LinkedIn Top Startup in 2019. We\u2019re continuing to grow and are looking for incredible talent that can help us achieve our mission. Robinhood is headquartered in Menlo Park, California, with offices in Lake Mary, Florida, Denver, Colorado, and London, UK. About the Role The finance and control group is primarily responsible for the firm compliance with SEC, FINRA and other regulatory agencies rules and regulations. The group compiles, reviews and prepares regulatory and financial reporting of the company, including but not limited to, customer and PAB reserve computation (SEA Rule 15c3-3), net capital computation 15c3-1 and FOCUS with all the supplemental schedules. The financial analyst will be in charge of preparing and assisting in producing these computations and reports. We are looking for a Financial Analyst to join our Finance and regulatory reporting team. In this newly created role, you will interact and coordinate with colleagues in Product, Business Solution, Accounting, back Office Operation, Compliance and other departments across the Company to ensure Finance and Regulatory Reporting group is ready for the launch of new products and the implementation of new process or change in exciting process. This position will also help out our group in periodical book closing and preparation of regulatory reporting and computations Your day to day will involve: Provide ownership of projects related to new products and/or process and ensure Finance and Regulatory reporting group readiness before implementations. Create and run queries to validate and support key reports and controls. Support project analysis, validation of plans, and ad-hoc requests/ Working with the business team for future plans. Review key reports and trends daily and research significant differences using available resources. Participate in strategic data analysis, research, and modeling for company leadership Follow up on project updates and provide up to date information to the group. Assist in preparation of monthly regulatory reports, including FOCUS and supplemental schedules Correspond with various other departments, discussing company plans and agreeing on future paths to be taken. Prepare accurate and complete reconciliation of ledgers and research to ensure open items and discrepancies are resolved in a timely manner. Prepare/assist weekly and month end customer and PAB reserve computation as per SEA Rule 15c3-3. Some things we consider critical for this role: At the minimum bachelor\u2019s degree in accounting. Knowledge of financial reporting and data mining tools such as SQL, Access, etc. Able to apply accounting concepts and policies in the preparation and review of financial transactions which may include but are not limited to, inter-company transactions, high volume complex accruals and prepaid expenses across a large number of accounts and monthly re-classes. Knowledge and experience of internal control over financial reporting and compliance (ICFR and ICOC). 3-5 years in accounting/finance experience Bonus Points: Have a working knowledge of SEA Rule 15c3-1, 15c3-3 Experience in broker dealer accounting Has series 27 license or willing and able to get one. CPA or MBA Feeling ready to give 100% to democratizing finance for all? We\u2019d love to have you apply, even if you feel unsure about whether you meet every single requirement in this posting. At Robinhood, we\u2019re looking for people invigorated by our mission, not just those who simp